title: Campbell County HS Shooting Incident Report

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Tennessee Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

The incident report and any supplements, such as police narratives, produced in relation to the shooting incident at Campbell County High School on November 8, 2005.

In the event that there are fees, I would request a waiver, as I am a member of a nonprofit media outlet and these records will be used in the public interest. The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes. 

I would prefer the request filed electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kent Hoover, a citizen of Tennessee, in coordination with Ben Baker.

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Hunter Biden Atlanta visit
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Records related to Hunter Biden's travel or activities on Saturday, August 12th, 2023, which included a visit to Congregation Etz Chaim in Marietta, GA, as well as a trampoline park. 

Mr. Biden's travel to Atlanta was first reported by the Atlanta Journal-Constitution (https://www.ajc.com/politics/politics-blog/the-jolt-hunter-biden-visits-atlanta-as-federal-investigation-expands/5WSXZR2VLBECNLM42UJWXA4K4E/) and is generally known to the public. 

Specifically, I am requesting the following categories of records related to the above, in addition to any other records related to the USSS' protective operations for Hunter Biden ("Chieftain") on 8/12/23:
a. Memos
b. Agendas/schedules/itineraries/calendars
c. Emails
d. Threat analysis 
e. Intelligence
f. Reports

I am also requesting all emails containing the terms "Etz Chaim" or "Marietta" from 7/1/23 until the date that this request is received.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Landon Edwards
